Coffee shop by day and wine bar vibes at night. Check us out for natural wines, local craft beers, and a selection of handmade cocktails, as well as, light far served from open to close. We have a small but excellent selection of wines to go as well. With the largest selection of natural wines in Mint Hill.
Whether your thing is coffee, tea, boba, fresh hand-squeezed lemonade, beer, wine or anything in between this is the place to go for absolutely delicious beverages all day long.

reviews_data.review_text: Best coffee in Mint Hill! Great atmosphere, friendly staff, and consistently excellent drinks. Love this place.

Colin has done great with this place. Using Cairn Coffee beans makes great coffee. Staff is always friendly and willing to patiently help with a smile. The snack foods offered are great. Plenty of semi-private nooks to meet someone and hang out for a while.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Steve! Your crew is helping to fill in a sink hole at my house right now, where do I review that? They’re doing a great job. (I don’t know if it’s your crew but I keep thinking I’m going to see you roll up and check out the work)

reviews_data.review_text: Great staff. Great location.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Rhonda!

reviews_data.review_text:
It’s like the quieter Breakman’s.
I loved the drink variety, you can get coffee and if you stay long enough, treat yourself to cocktail hour.
The staff is kind and the seasonal syrups are so fun to play around with.
Highly recommend!

Still love the space and atmosphere. Unfortunately since they changed syrups to be homemade a few months ago, the flavors just aren't noticeable any more. Wish they could make the flavors stronger again.
Cool coffee and libation house in mint hill. Owner is very creative.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey, thanks for that! I appreciate you appreciate me and the shop!

reviews_data.review_text:
Tough visit today, decided to venture out for the first time here. Will note that it was quite busy, and a tight space. Cute design on the interior. Fiancee ordered seasonal cherry latte, and I a cold-brew. Staff were understandably overwhelmed, but were brusque with us and other customers despite our patience.

Not sure if it was just today, but either way disappointing. Probably won’t come back :(
reviews_data.owner_answer: I’m so sorry to hear that. We had a very busy Sunday, much more than normal, and we will put extra people on moving forward. So sorry you had a bad experience.

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place and there weekly coffees! The Dubai chocolate was my fav!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Briana! We love you loving us. We will see you at the shop soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely the cutest coffee house of ALL !! Our first time here and we just loved every bit of it. Great coffee, small bites, wine, staff service so perf, and such a great atmosphere !! Great seating inside and out … l o v e l y. A new FAV !! ♥️☕️☕️♥️
reviews_data.owner_answer: This is the most 5 star written 4 star review we’ve ever received. Thank you so much. I love a challenge and I’ll earn that last ⭐️!!!!

reviews_data.review_text: This place is so cute! My dirty chai was also really good, will definitely come again.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Myles! Thanks friend. We're so glad you stopped by and we can't wait to see you again. Thanks for joining our little community.

reviews_data.review_text:
Cute place, kinda hidden to be honest so maybe slow down and pay attention so you don’t miss your turn. Looking at the map, I almost missed it. You park around the back, plenty of parking and walk in from one door through another room and go toward the front to order. It seems like there are several rooms you can chill in I saw some people reading and with their laptops, etc. nice concept.
Only had one size which is fine (16oz) about $6.50 with a little flavoring and a plant-based milk. coffee was good.
I really like the outside seating in the front with the shades over the tables and fake turf. Really cute, they did a good job with this place! I’ll probably come back soon to study here.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey thanks so much! That's all so nice to hear. We went with one size for our iced drinks so that you can taste our single origin espresso beans, any larger and it would require more shots of espresso. But here's a secret, if you bring a mug, we don't care what size it is, we'll fill it! 

Thanks for visiting us and we hope to see you again real soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Went there Sunday night with my wife for a drink after seeing on Instagram they also serve craft cocktails. It did not disappoint. Cocktails were delicious and the vibe on the porch was super chill with a great playlist. They even had 100% agave mezcal! Will definatly be back again for another Mezcal Mule. Highly recommend if your looking for coffee or cocktails in Mint Hill.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey David, thanks for the great review! I can’t wait send this to the bartender who helped you out tonight. I’m a Mezcal guy, btw, so we’ll always have the real stuff in stock.

reviews_data.review_text:
We LOVE forest trail. Their coffees and treats are delicious! Very family friendly. The owners, Colin and Kristen, are wonderful people.

They support other local businesses by carrying family dough bagels, having local vendor markets, having other small businesses goodies available for purchase in their shop, and having locally grown flowers available sometimes.

They have SUPER FUN events like their monthly mom meet up (which has wonderful moms EVERY time), their vendor markets, trivia, and more.

The indoor space is great for working, socializing, and everything in between. They have comfortable seating and great vibes. The outdoor space is SOOO nice during any season with the shade for summer and the heaters for winter.

reviews_data.review_text: Both coffee orders wrong. Hot pour-over was luke warm at best. Lavender matcha had vanilla, no lavender.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Sorry to hear that Brian. We would happily fix these problems if you brought them to us in person rather than taking to the internet. Now there’s nothing we can do other than apologize. We certainly aren’t perfect and mistakes will happen from time to time. Again, sorry we failed you this trip. 

We do bring our water temp to 195 for pour overs but if it ended up too cold we will happily remake it next time. 

Thanks for visiting and we will do our best to be better next time you come see us.

reviews_data.review_text: I liked this place okay. I mean it's not the worst experience but I just went here after attending a car meetup just up the street. I would say their matcha latte is okay but their cookie bar is good. It's got a good atmosphere with plenty of seating for guests, both indoor and outdoor which is nice. Service was great and the young man was polite which I would say is the highlight of my visit. Service is always done best with a positive attitude. 😁

Cute local coffee shop offering pastries and bagels, coffee, beer, wine and other local offerings. Have plenty of spaces for small groups to hang and work. 2 outdoor patios, 2 porches, and 2 small rooms. Parking is limited,
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks John! Glad you enjoyed your visit with us and we hope to see you again real soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I did a search for coffee, houses or coffee nearby and found this quaint house with excellent cappuccino and bakery
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the review JD! Glad you enjoyed yourself at our spot. Hope to see you again sometime.

reviews_data.review_text:
I recently visited the Forest Trail House for coffee with a friend. We found this coffee shop quite delightful. They have repurposed an old home through thoughtful use of space and design. When you enter, you're greeted with fresh plants and floral bouquets available for purchase. Meandering through you'll see rooms with ample seating, a game selection and cozy outdoor area. Coffee and pastries were delicious with a great selection. We enjoyed our time here and will be visiting again!

As a tip, the driveway is slightly hidden but runs alongside the right side of the house (when looking straight at it) with parking in the rear. It is a single car driveway so that can prove to be a bit tricky when it's busy.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much for this review! Reading this was such a lovely way to start my week. 

We are secretly working on solutions for the driveway. Well, not secretly but it involves the state so maybe slowly is the better way to put it. Hopefully, within the next 6 months we'll have a much better driveway situation. Thankfully, our customers are patient and kind and treat each other with so much respect in our driveway. 

Thank you again! It means the world to us to know people like you are loving what we are doing.

reviews_data.review_text:
This review is for the manager/owners, the barista today was awesome & truly
doing the best he could being the only person tagged on a May Sunday afternoon. I waited 40 minutes for an iced latte with 5 orders in front of me. I got one of the seasonal lattes & had to ask for the cold foam in the drink description to be put on the drink when it was handed to me - again, this is really on Scheduling & Management to provide enough coverage or to place a sign about wait times & short coverage. I have learned my lesson on “stopping by for a coffee” & think I’ll try coming in for a cocktail at night, maybe….. If you’re coming to read or get some work done with headphones & are going to be there a while, you’ll love it, but if you’re trying to be away from your house or errands for a total of almost 1 hr between parking ordering & waiting (the 40 min was my wait alone) go elsewhere.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Soul, thanks for the compliments about our barista. We love our staff so much! 

This isn't a normal situation and I appreciate your thoughts on it. Our wait times are generally 10 minutes or less. I assure you that when it's as busy as it was this past Sunday we have two people on, at least. But for nearly 104 Sundays in a row the hour in question, has never once been that busy. It's generally our slowest time of the week, actually. The hour before you came and the hour after you came were very slow as well. In fact, the final two hours of Sunday barely covered payroll for 1 person working. Every now and again we'll get caught in a situation like this and I will generally drop whatever I'm doing and shoot in to help. That's the nature of having a small business. Yesterday I was an hour away from the shop so I couldn't but my wife did come in, it must have been just after you left because when the alert hit my phone that you had left this review, she was there helping. 

Again, this is a very strange occurrence. It's almost bizarre how predictable the flow of traffic is here, often, week to week we are within $5 of the previous week's sales for any given hour. Sometimes it's exactly the same and that's when we worry about the simulation having glitches. But the hour you were here was 8 times, literally, the money we did the previous 4 weeks at that hour. Regardless, we are switching the schedule because I don't want anyone to have this happen to them again. 

As a small business owner I spend hours considering small changes like this because of the rippling effect it has on our entire business. I assure you that nothing is done around here without careful consideration followed by heavy anxiety, and finished off with "just praying we made the right decision." We take all of these suggestions, problems, and complaints very seriously and we dwell on them much more than the compliments. 

Again, sorry your experience wasn't what you were hoping that day. We won't let that happen again.

reviews_data.review_text: Haven't been in years decided to stop by with my sister. The girl with curly hair taking our order was very friendly. I ordered a regular Latte, my sister ordered a decaf latte. Once we got our drinks my sister wanted to make sure her drink was decaf so she asked, they let us know we had them mixed up. The barista with long straight hair then proceeded to make the comment "Oh I assumed it was that bc pregnant people aren't supposed drink caffeine." Yes, I am visibly pregnant and was quickly bummed hearing that. I can say more but overall it tainted our experience to us not even drinking our drinks. Please, just take a moment..
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hanlon's Razor says; "Never attribute malice that which can be explained by lack of experience or naivty," and I think that's a nice reminder for us all. We have several regulars who are also pregnant who have made the chose to abstain from caffeine. Our barista, with whom I spoke, made that assumption on whose coffee was whose, based on those few regulars. I'm sorry that this tainted your experience but I can assure you no malice was intended. She is easily one of our customer's favorite baristas because she wears her kindness on her sleeve. She's nothing if not sweet. Anyway, sorry your experience wasn't what you had hoped for and congratulations on your pregnancy!

reviews_data.review_text: The atmosphere of the café was very warm and cozy. The service was also very good.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you kindly, friend.

reviews_data.review_text:
This coffee shop is such a hidden gem, people working there are lovely and so is their coffee and pastries. I enjoy trying all their new monthly flavors and its a great place to work/study.
I do wish they sold more savory options like sandwiches or wraps (but I believe its something planned for the future).
The only other thing is if you plan on working in the evening, check their calendar because they do have events and it can get very loud and I had to leave early due to noise and lack of space on few occasions.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much Vicki! We do have a lot of events, that is true. Usually, Thursday, and Saturdays, and trivia Fridays happens outside now that it's warm again (if you're reading this in January of 2026 just know I'm writing it in Spring.)

We are working on our food trailer as I type this. Honestly, I'm typing this to avoid that work. No, I'm kidding but we are hoping to have savory food, cooked right here, within the coming weeks. And as for wraps and sandwiches I literally just bought some so we are adding "grab and go" (or "grab and sit and hang out and work or read") options as of this afternoon. We're excited about that. 

Best practice is to check our instagram: @foresttrailhouse to see if we have anything going on that evening or what our specials are and just to keep up to date. Thanks so much for this lovely review. We'll see you at the shop soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I wanna like this place everytime I go, but unfortunately leave disappointed. Their food is very mediocre, and the coffee is too. Their lattes never taste like what they say they are, and usually taste like they have no syrup at all. I think their aesthetic is perfect, but seems like that’s what their main focus is on, instead of good drinks & good food.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry you feel this way Austin. We are always happy to add more syrup if that's what you'd like. I will defend that our drinks and food take up 90% of our bandwidth and the aesthetic is a distant third. Our espresso was selected over weeks of trail and error, it's a single origin from the Huehuetenaga region Guatemala. We do feel like the syrup should be the cherry on top of the sundae and not the sundae itself. We want you to taste the espresso and milk more than the syrup, otherwise, it becomes too sweet for us but that's just us and everyone has their own desires and ultimately we're there to please so just ask for extra syrup and we'll gladly give that to you. Our house blend for our is also a Guatemalan blend that we chose because most people like a medium dark blend. But if you really want a nice light blend you should try our pour over! It's amazing. We make all of our food in house with trained bakers. I don't know what you ordered but I'm sorry it wasn't to your liking. We know we can't win 'em all but as a small business it always hurts to get reviews like this. We take it personally and try to learn from it.

reviews_data.review_text: Best coffee and frappe
reviews_data.owner_answer: Short, sweet, 5 stars. We love it, thanks!!!

reviews_data.review_text: This is my favorite coffee spot in all of Charlotte! I’m here every day, enjoying one of the monthly rotating pastries and an expertly made latte. FTH has literally been a lifeline since moving to Mint Hill. I’ve met so many amazing friends here and it’s because they foster a lovely and welcoming environment that attracts all the best people! Tip your baristas well and treat them right or I will come for you ;)
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Minna!!! We love seeing you here and as not one of the baristas/bartenders I agree, tip them well! They're working their butts off and doing an amazing job here creating a wonderful space in Mint Hill. We're very proud of this staff!

reviews_data.review_text:
This used to be our favorite coffe place because they have a wall of pictures of dogs in the shop and we found them to be very dog friendly to well behaved dogs such as ours. This put Forest Trail above other local coffee shops especially in the winter.
Today we were informed their policy has changed and we were asked to leave with our pup. There was no other customers in the store but we respected their decision and left. For us Forest Hill has lost the one attraction that set them apart from the other coffee shops so it's a matter of if their coffee is good enough to sit outside in the cold. You can probably get the same combination of syrups at McDonalds, Starbucks or Brakemans. Forest Trail should probably take down all the pictures of cute dogs in their shop.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry about that Jon, it’s not our favorite rule either. You can go to ncleg.gov and see who you can write about changing it but our hands are tied. The pics will stay though, sorry. We love our outdoor pups. Also, we certainly aim to be much better than those other places and we’ll continue to push our drinks to new and better places. Anyway, sorry you were upset today. It’s been our policy since day one because it’s the law. So is it a policy? IDK, honestly, it’s just the law.

reviews_data.review_text: So cozy . I went there for a mom's meeting and i loved the place. Now i plan to come back with family and enjoy the front yard

reviews_data.owner_answer: That's amazing to hear! Thanks so much. We're so glad you had a great time, make sure to follow us on IG @foresttrailhouse to see all of our events, we do a lot, and many of them are geared towards entertaining the kiddos.

reviews_data.review_text:
Relaxing coffee shop. Plenty of seating inside and outside. Very pleasant service. Espresso was good, but it is served in a paper cup(hence, the 4 stars). I travel with my own cup for such situations!

Based on new information, I can’t fault Forest Trail for following the law! Good espresso AND high ethics! I’m changing my review all 5 stars! Thanks for my relaxing visit!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
You’re always welcomed to use your own cup Kent. We are made to serve all disposals by the state of North Carolina, unfortunately. And we would never go against that rule. The ceramic cups you see behind the bar are for show only. We would neeeeever use them. But you can always ask us next time. Maybe we’ll change that policy. 

Anyway, glad you enjoyed your stop with us!

reviews_data.review_text: It's such a cozy home style coffee shop. Has nice sitting areas, even for a larger group of ppl to sit, I went with friends and enjoyed it. I ordered the chai latte 😋
reviews_data.owner_answer: Love it, Almond! Thanks for visiting us. 💙

reviews_data.review_text: Love going here! It's our favorite spot to get coffee and hang out in town. We also did a paint by numbers night that was really fun. The service is always great and they have great indoor and outdoor seating available.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Kim! This is so nice to read.

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place, one of my top coffee shops in the Charlotte Area. Surprisingly one of the best margs I’ve ever had as well
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much! We love to hear this.

reviews_data.review_text: Always 5 star foŕ wonderful ambience...coffee...atmosphere 🤩😍
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Nis! We are glad you love us as much as we love you loving us.

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee was okay not the best, nice little house has good atmosphere. The reason for the low rating is the service at the front. The girls working were acting like it was a huge inconvenience for me to order something, made no effort to be kind in any way, not even a hello or smile. Made me feel like I should have just gone to Starbucks so at least the coffee would be worth it.
reviews_data.owner_answer: I’m so sorry to hear that Emily. We will correct this situation.

reviews_data.review_text: Cute little coffee shop with baked goods. Americano was excellent, Mr would’ve preferred the drip coffee be hotter. Almond swirl pastry was a little oily, blueberry muffin was excellent. Service is great, the ladies working this morning were happy ams friendly. Go here!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much! So glad you had a great time with us.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to have coffee/tea and a pastry. Feels like you are in someone's home. Especially nice sitting outside with a screened porch.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Kathy! This sounds like a 5 star review so we’re just going to pretend that’s what it is.

reviews_data.review_text: Super cute little place, and the barista even made “out of season” drinks for us that we really wanted to try!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Yay! We're so glad you had a nice experience.

reviews_data.review_text: This place is always amazing! Love their pumpkin chai latte. Also have had some of their baked goods which were also amazing. I love the fact that they have a bouncy house for the kids so the adults can enjoy their coffee. Definitely a big plus.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Brittany! We love being loved!

reviews_data.review_text: Love the porch and the rocking chairs while having a coffee.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Arthur! Glad you had a nice morning with us.

reviews_data.review_text: Saw the reviews and went out of our way to bring our family here. Spent $40, and threw our drinks out on the way out. Sticky bun and cookie was good! The service was less than kind. Worst coffee we’ve ever had. The outdoor area was AWESOME for the kids, but the bathroom reeked of urine. Won’t be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Piper, I really am truly so sorry you had a bad experience. We strive to be better than this and I take it very personally whenever a customer has a bad experience. I understand why you won't be coming back.

For people who aren't Piper who are reading this, the way to handle this is to come to us and say you aren't happy. She ordered two fresh squeezed lemonades, which we can easily adjust to your liking, making them sweeter or more tart, however you like it. We squeeze them fresh so we can definitely help you with that! She also ordered our cold brew with a cold foam and a latte - again, these are all adjustable and if somethings wrong, please come to us. We will fix it for you.

If you're at a small business and the bathroom is dirty believe me, we're more embarrassed than you are. But there are also customers who do not care and make a mess. Please tell us. Please. Sometimes we'll got hours without being able to get into the bathrooms because we're so busy, but if you tell us, or other small businesses, we'll get in there and fix the problem. 

Small businesses rely on your input because we cannot be everywhere at all times. So tell us in the moment if you can. That way we can help. If you wait and do it on the internet, it's impossible for it to fix it for YOU.

reviews_data.review_text:
Cute coffee shop. Would love to sit and work here. friendly staff
They even have board games
My almond frappe was really, really good! Wish my almond twist wasnt super cold. Made it hard to eat.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey sorry your twist was cold. We should’ve warned it up for you. Next time we will! Thanks for stopping by.

reviews_data.review_text: I absolutely LOVE this place!! They donsuch an amazing job with everything!! My fave is the thin mint mocha!! 💙
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much!

reviews_data.review_text: This place is vibes✨ The prices are so good compared to other charlotte coffee shops!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Gabriella! Appreciate you.

reviews_data.review_text: Today, wife was looking for a pistachio latte.  Fortunately for us, Forrest Trail was literally right around the corner from us. I called to see if they had it.  They did!!!! My wife was very pleased!!!! We found i our coffee shop now!!!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Yay! It was great meeting you. Let me know who that other coffee shop was up north with pistachio and I’ll send them a thank you note for the new customers.

reviews_data.review_text:
Cold brew was good, pastries were okay, just a tiny bit too sweet for my taste.

However, my latte was not great, almost half of it was foam, and the bouncy house out front was less than relaxing.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry you didn’t have the best experience. Weekends can get a little crazy sometimes but we love our little customers too.

reviews_data.review_text: Owners and staff are amazing! Coffee shop is super welcoming and great for a lol date with the kiddos! They have a bounce house outside weather permitting! We had a meeting here and they were super accommodating!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Jessica! We are so glad you're loving what we're doing.

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place!!  The owners are super sweet and present.  The snack selection is wonderful.  They have curated speciality items from all over  (like my favorite, their Wisconsin Cheese).  They have a wide variety of drinks too.  Lots of options for kids and adults.  I highly recommend this Mint Hill gem!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Angelica!! This feels so great on a day when a tropical storm has us hiding while our power flickers on and off all day. Hope to see you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped by to get some coffee and treat for my wife. Coffee is tasty and hot but to my disappointment they only had full whipping cream and half and half,  no other healthier alternatives. Ordered two cinnamon rolls and they offered to heat them but I took them as is. Got to the car and mine was dry and hard, like it was old. Tried heating the second one when I got home and bleh, day old rolls. Kind  of an expensive $20 lesson for me but the coffee was good.
reviews_data.owner_answer: I'm sorry to hear that the cinnamon rolls weren't your favorites. For future reference we will always tell you when everything was baked, I know that those rolls were baked 8 hours before you came in, I went and checked in the system. We also have oat milk, unsweetened Almond milk, whole milk, and skim milk in case you decide to give us another try, which we hope you do!

reviews_data.review_text: Always love coming here, staff is great and the coffee is delicious! Great meeting spot to catch up with friends or talking business.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Stephanie!

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent service, great coffees, I love this place!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We love you! Thanks for the kind review.

reviews_data.review_text: We continued our quest of trying out the local coffee shops in the greater Charlotte area and ended up here.  We ordered food, coffee, and tea.  The coffee was a light/medium roast and was quite good but not our personal favorite.  The tea was excellent.  We ordered the quiche and a stinger.  The quiche was amazing but the stinger was super dry, did not contain much meat, and was difficult to eat.  We would not get the stinger again but we would eat the quiche all day long.  The location is great and there is plenty of parking out back.  The atmosphere here was really great.  We will definitely be back if only for the quiche and to try a different type of coffee.  Nice place to chill out if you are in the Mint Hill area!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Oh man, that's a bummer about the stinger! We love our stingers and it's a bummer that we missed on that one. We make everything in house and take a lot of pride in our work, we're really sorry we didn't nail it for you. Next time you should try our pour over or ask for one of our roasts in a french press, I love Cairn coffee and that's why we work with them. We've found that most of our customers love a slightly darker roast but we have lighter roasts available by the cup as well. It'll just take us a few extra minutes. Anyway, we appreciate you giving us a try! Good luck in your continued quest.

reviews_data.review_text: One of the best chai tea’s I have had in a long time, there is a lot of space indoors and outside and it has a very relaxed atmosphere. The staff are extremely warm and welcoming, it feels more like going to a friends house then a shop.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Steven! We're glad you had such a good experience.

reviews_data.review_text: My family went on a warm day. There were lots of people enjoying the outdoors so we consumed our coffees and pastries inside. It was spacious, quiet, and cool. The staff were friendly. The coffees and pastries were delicious and inexpensive.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! We are so glad you had a nice time and we hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Since moving to the area, it has been a great study spot for me with a great range of seating inside and outside. They also have a couple boardgames you can play with others while there.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks friend!

reviews_data.review_text: How I love this place! Has been going for almost a year, it grows on me. The place is unique compared to other local coffee shops. When we got to the counter we were met with a rude, blank stare just waiting for our order with no hello or welcome, and then a "what are you having". I told the girl it was our first time there and we didn't see the coffee menu (to explain our delay in ordering) and she just stood there with no reply, no beckoning to where the menu was, nor a recommendation. We eventually looked around and found the menu and ordered 2 Americanos (we would've ordered more with suggestion or even friendliness but decided against it). After getting our EXTREMELY HOT coffees, we tried adding sugar to them but it melted the straws and couldn't stir. After getting into the car, the coffees were too hot to drink and started to warp the lids and coffee cups. Now I'm sitting here, pulled over in a parking lot writing this review with hot coffee ALL OVER ME and my car because just picking the cup up made the coffee burst up from the cup, popping up the lid. I STILL haven't even gotten a chance to taste my coffee! If I had the time I would've gone back to complain in person. The sad part is that if the service had been better, friendlier, maybe I wouldn't be as upset, but her rudeness almost made me feel as if this was almost on purpose....as a person of color, I would hate to think this was the reason for a 4.9 reviewed coffee house to deliver such poor service...

reviews_data.review_text:
I recently visited the Forest Trail House for coffee with a friend. We found this coffee shop quite delightful. They have repurposed an old home through thoughtful use of space and design. We are secretly working on solutions for the driveway. Well, not secretly but it involves the state so maybe slowly is the better way to put it. Thank you again! It means the world to us to know people like you are loving what we are doing.

reviews_data.review_text:
This review is for the manager/owners, the barista today was awesome & truly
doing the best he could being the only person tagged on a May Sunday afternoon. I waited 40 minutes for an iced latte with 5 orders in front of me. I got one of the seasonal lattes & had to ask for the cold foam in the drink description to be put on the drink when it was handed to me - again, this is really on Scheduling & Management to provide enough coverage or to place a sign about wait times & short coverage. I have learned my lesson on “stopping by for a coffee” & think I’ll try coming in for a cocktail at night, maybe….. If you’re coming to read or get some work done with headphones & are going to be there a while, you’ll love it, but if you’re trying to be away from your house or errands for a total of almost 1 hr between parking ordering & waiting (the 40 min was my wait alone) go elsewhere.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Soul, thanks for the compliments about our barista. We love our staff so much! 

This isn't a normal situation and I appreciate your thoughts on it. Our wait times are generally 10 minutes or less. I assure you that when it's as busy as it was this past Sunday we have two people on, at least. But for nearly 104 Sundays in a row the hour in question, has never once been that busy. It's generally our slowest time of the week, actually. The hour before you came and the hour after you came were very slow as well. In fact, the final two hours of Sunday barely covered payroll for 1 person working. Every now and again we'll get caught in a situation like this and I will generally drop whatever I'm doing and shoot in to help. That's the nature of having a small business. Yesterday I was an hour away from the shop so I couldn't but my wife did come in, it must have been just after you left because when the alert hit my phone that you had left this review, she was there helping. 

Again, this is a very strange occurrence. It's almost bizarre how predictable the flow of traffic is here, often, week to week we are within $5 of the previous week's sales for any given hour. Sometimes it's exactly the same and that's when we worry about the simulation having glitches. But the hour you were here was 8 times, literally, the money we did the previous 4 weeks at that hour. Regardless, we are switching the schedule because I don't want anyone to have this happen to them again. 

As a small business owner I spend hours considering small changes like this because of the rippling effect it has on our entire business. I assure you that nothing is done around here without careful consideration followed by heavy anxiety, and finished off with "just praying we made the right decision." We take all of these suggestions, problems, and complaints very seriously and we dwell on them much more than the compliments. 

Again, sorry your experience wasn't what you were hoping that day. We won't let that happen again.

reviews_data.review_text: Haven't been in years decided to stop by with my sister. The girl with curly hair taking our order was very friendly. I ordered a regular Latte, my sister ordered a decaf latte. Once we got our drinks my sister wanted to make sure her drink was decaf so she asked, they let us know we had them mixed up. The barista with long straight hair then proceeded to make the comment "Oh I assumed it was that bc pregnant people aren't supposed drink caffeine." Yes, I am visibly pregnant and was quickly bummed hearing that. I can say more but overall it tainted our experience to us not even drinking our drinks. Please, just take a moment..
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hanlon's Razor says; "Never attribute malice that which can be explained by lack of experience or naivty," and I think that's a nice reminder for us all. We have several regulars who are also pregnant who have made the chose to abstain from caffeine. Our barista, with whom I spoke, made that assumption on whose coffee was whose, based on those few regulars. I'm sorry that this tainted your experience but I can assure you no malice was intended. She is easily one of our customer's favorite baristas because she wears her kindness on her sleeve. She's nothing if not sweet. Anyway, sorry your experience wasn't what you had hoped for and congratulations on your pregnancy!

We are working on our food trailer as I type this. Honestly, I'm typing this to avoid that work. No, I'm kidding but we are hoping to have savory food, cooked right here, within the coming weeks. And as for wraps and sandwiches I literally just bought some so we are adding "grab and go" (or "grab and sit and hang out and work or read") options as of this afternoon. We're excited about that.

reviews_data.review_text: I wanna like this place everytime I go, but unfortunately leave disappointed. Their food is very mediocre, and the coffee is too. Their lattes never taste like what they say they are, and usually taste like they have no syrup at all. I think their aesthetic is perfect, but seems like that’s what their main focus is on, instead of good drinks & good food.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry you feel this way Austin. We are always happy to add more syrup if that's what you'd like. I will defend that our drinks and food take up 90% of our bandwidth and the aesthetic is a distant third. Our espresso was selected over weeks of trail and error, it's a single origin from the Huehuetenaga region Guatemala. We do feel like the syrup should be the cherry on top of the sundae and not the sundae itself. We want you to taste the espresso and milk more than the syrup, otherwise, it becomes too sweet for us but that's just us and everyone has their own desires and ultimately we're there to please so just ask for extra syrup and we'll gladly give that to you. Our house blend for our is also a Guatemalan blend that we chose because most people like a medium dark blend. But if you really want a nice light blend you should try our pour over! It's amazing. We make all of our food in house with trained bakers. I don't know what you ordered but I'm sorry it wasn't to your liking. We know we can't win 'em all but as a small business it always hurts to get reviews like this. We take it personally and try to learn from it.

reviews_data.review_text:

reviews_data.review_text: Okay so....today was my first time trying this coffee shop. My husband and I were out running errands and I needed a pick me up so instead trying to find a Starbucks we wanted to try local instead, which is what we prefer. Upon entering, the atmosphere is very chill and quaint, but the service was extremely lacking. When we got to the counter we were met with a rude, blank stare just waiting for our order with no hello or welcome, and then a "what are you having". I told the girl it was our first time there and we didn't see the coffee menu (to explain our delay in ordering) and she just stood there with no reply, no beckoning to where the menu was, nor a recommendation. We eventually looked around and found the menu and ordered 2 Americanos (we would've ordered more with suggestion or even friendliness but decided against it). After getting our EXTREMELY HOT coffees, we tried adding sugar to them but it melted the straws and couldn't stir. After getting into the car, the coffees were too hot to drink and started to warp the lids and coffee cups.
